_json.description: Did you know?   Now is the time to get community/feral cats fixed before they start reproducing. Friends of BCAS knows the only way to stop the killing of cats at our shelter is to prevent new litters. Starting in February, spay/neuter of community/feral cats is free and pet cats only $20. This is for Burlington County residents only.  Visit our spay/neuter webpage to make an appointment. Friends also provides assistance to trap-neuter-return community cats you feed. IF YOU FEED THEM, FIX THEM.
